# Hugo Larochelle (1983-Present)

## Overview
Hugo Larochelle is a Canadian computer scientist and research scientist at Google Brain, where he previously led the Google Brain team in Montreal. He is an Associate Professor at the Université de Montréal and a core academic member of Mila - Quebec AI Institute. Larochelle is known for his work on deep learning, particularly in the areas of neural networks, meta-learning, and few-shot learning.

